      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "LLM-as-Judge Faithfulness Grader"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "For production eval pipelines, a faithfulness grader can be run as part of your eval suite on sampled traffic:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "FAITHFULNESS_RUBRIC = \"\"\"\nYou are evaluating whether an AI answer is faithful to the provided source documents.\n\nSources:\n{sources}\n\nQuestion: {question}\nAnswer: {answer}\n\nScore the answer on faithfulness (0.0 \u2013 1.0):\n- 1.0: Every claim in the answer is directly supported by the sources. No facts beyond sources.\n- 0.7: Mostly supported; minor interpretive leap present.\n- 0.4: Some claims are unsupported or contradict sources.\n- 0.0: Answer contains fabricated facts not in any source.\n\nRespond JSON: {{\"score\": float, \"unsupported_claims\": [\"...\"], \"explanation\": \"one sentence\"}}\n\"\"\"\n\ndef faithfulness_score(\n    question: str,\n    answer: str,\n    sources: list[dict],\n    model: str = \"claude-opus-4-8\"\n) -> dict:\n    import json\n    source_text = \"\\n\".join(\n        f\"[{i+1}] {s['title']}:\\n{s['text']}\"\n        for i, s in enumerate(sources)\n    )\n    prompt = FAITHFULNESS_RUBRIC.format(\n        sources=source_text, question=question, answer=answer\n    )\n    resp = client.messages.create(\n        model=model,\n        max_tokens=256,\n        messages=[{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": prompt}]\n    )\n    return json.loads(resp.content[0].text)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Handling the \"I Don't Know\" Path"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A grounded system must gracefully handle questions the retrieved sources cannot answer. Without an explicit fallback, Claude may synthesize an answer from training knowledge \u2014 exactly the hallucination grounding is meant to prevent. Two failure modes arise:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "False grounding:"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " Claude cites a source that does not actually contain the answer, fabricating a fact and attributing it."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Silent extrapolation:"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " Claude gives a correct-seeming answer from training data with no citation, masking the retrieval gap."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Detect unanswerable queries by monitoring for the exact fallback phrase you specified in the system prompt. Route these to a secondary knowledge source, surface them to a human, or log them as retrieval gaps for index improvement:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "FALLBACK_PHRASE = \"The provided sources do not contain this information.\"\n\ndef grounded_answer(\n    query: str,\n    docs: list[dict],\n    model: str = \"claude-opus-4-8\"\n) -> dict:\n    messages, system = build_grounded_prompt(query, docs)\n    resp = client.messages.create(\n        model=model, max_tokens=1024,\n        system=system, messages=messages\n    )\n    text = resp.content[0].text.strip()\n    unanswerable = FALLBACK_PHRASE in text\n    return {\n        \"answer\": text,\n        \"unanswerable\": unanswerable,\n        \"citations\": [] if unanswerable else extract_citations(text),\n        \"source_count\": len(docs)\n    }\n\ndef route_unanswerable(result: dict, query: str) -> None:\n    if result[\"unanswerable\"]:\n        # Log retrieval gap for index improvement\n        log_retrieval_gap(query)\n        # Optionally escalate to broader search or human review\n        trigger_escalation(query)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Retrieval Quality and Grounding Quality"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Grounding does not fix poor retrieval. If the retrieved documents do not contain the answer, Claude cannot be grounded and accurate simultaneously \u2014 it can only be grounded and say \"I don't know.\" Grounding quality is therefore an upper bound set by retrieval quality."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When faithfulness scores are high but answer accuracy is low, the problem is retrieval, not grounding. Diagnose by logging which queries hit the fallback phrase \u2014 these identify index gaps. When faithfulness scores are low, the problem is grounding instruction strength. Strengthen the system prompt and add a citation verifier."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "blockquote",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "A useful heuristic: measure faithfulness and answer accuracy independently. Faithfulness measures whether Claude stays within sources. Accuracy measures whether those sources contain the correct answer. A system can be 100% faithful and still wrong \u2014 it correctly cited a wrong source."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Common Pitfalls"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
